{
  "stem": "11801.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was talking about the-- taking care of the necessary documentation in order to leave for the United States.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We had to make several trips to Antwerp to-- I guess the American consulate was located there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was not a long trip for us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had to take my brother a couple of times.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The last time we took him, which was the most important time, where he had to-- all of us had to swear that the information we had provided in our applications was the truth.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, anyone who gets a passport has to do that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The whole truth and nothing but the truth.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my brother all of a sudden decided he didn't want to do that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He didn't want to swear that the information provided was the truth.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, of course, immediately the, the official in charge questioned his mental state and the veracity of the information we had provided on his behalf.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I have to tell you that my mother had bribed a doctor to give him a, a clean bill of health.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Everyone was so hungry in Belgium, it wasn't difficult to bribe anyone.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my mother, being my mother, you know-- nothing fazed her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Survival was-- had become an art with her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And knowing which way to turn was her strength.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But at that point, there was nothing she could do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this time they-- the consul sent my brother to their doctor, who, of course, declared him mentally unfit.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So he was denied a visa.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And this was, of course, another blow for my mother, who had just found her children and now was about to lose one of them again, although she did feel that he was in good hands.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
